para.para.body:
Shift an object into a different location using a translation vector 
                     \Vect{a}
                  . Compare this with shifting the object twice as far in the same direction. The corresponding translation vector is 
                     2\Vect{a}
                  .

In general, shifting the object in the given direction  times as far as the original translation does has the translation vector 
                     t\cdot \Vect{a}
                  .
